    <title>The file search functions are not functioning properly when searching for words contenting in LibreOffice Documents</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Dear Sir / Madam,</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">I am a user of Libre Office on my Macbook Pro, and I notice that there are a few functions which are not operating properly on the latest Mac PC operating system when using Libre Office; and I'd be grateful if the team at Libre Office can assist in resolving these technical issues that I have listed below:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">A) When using the latest Mac PC OS file search function in 'All My Files' to search for Libre Office Documents.docx contenting search words that exist in documents, I notice that the systems are unable to detect documents contenting search words; if words in Libre Office Documents have punctuation marks next to the words.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">B) Additionally, the file search function in Mac PC OS for locating Libre Office Documents.docx are case sensitive.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">C) At times, the file search function is unable to find Libre Office Documents even though the search words matches exactly in the Libre Office File Documents</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">D) The file search function also unable to detect the word or words contenting in Libre Office Documents when a word or words are: highlighted, in another text colour, text font, font size or in other formats</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">C) Furthermore, these technical issues as stated above also occur when using the file search function in the desktop document folders on Mac PC OS.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">Your help is greatly appreciated.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">Best regards,</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="10">
            <sentence id="10.1">C. Chow
Date: 24th April 2016</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
